# ============================================
# BETA TIME OVERRIDE (Debug Builds Only)
# ============================================
#
# Freeze app time to a specific moment for testing historical data.
# Format: ISO8601 with timezone (YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ)
#
# When set:
# - App treats this value as "now"
# - Only completed and scheduled games appear
# - Live games are excluded
# - Orange "Testing mode" badge appears in app
#
# When unset:
# - App uses real system time (normal behavior)
#
# Examples:

# NBA Opening Night 2024-25
# IOS_BETA_ASSUME_NOW=2024-10-23T04:00:00Z

# Super Bowl LVIII (Feb 12, 2024)
# IOS_BETA_ASSUME_NOW=2024-02-12T04:00:00Z

# March Madness 2024 Final (Apr 9, 2024)
# IOS_BETA_ASSUME_NOW=2024-04-09T04:00:00Z

# Yesterday at 4:00 AM (useful for recent games)
# IOS_BETA_ASSUME_NOW=2025-01-08T04:00:00Z

# ============================================
# USAGE
# ============================================
#
# 1. Set the environment variable:
#    export IOS_BETA_ASSUME_NOW=2024-02-15T04:00:00Z
#
# 2. Launch the app from Xcode
#
# 3. Verify snapshot mode is active:
#    - Orange badge appears at top of home screen
#    - Console logs show "Time override enabled"
#
# 4. To disable:
#    unset IOS_BETA_ASSUME_NOW
#    # or use Admin Settings > Clear Override
#
# See docs/beta-time-override.md for full documentation.
